    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-11-25T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-11-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="928"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d928">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711C.02/11–2553: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alger</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-11-25T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 25, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>348. Reference Department telegrams 498, November 19 and 513, November 23.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d928fn1">For Department of State telegram 513, Nov. 23, see
                        footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_1468">p. 1468</ref>.</note> Department’s views
                    strongly urged on Foreign Office which refused to change instructions to Belgian
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> delegation. These instructions are to
                    abstain on Puerto Rican resolution, even if preambular paragraph is deleted.
                    Foreign Office considers that wording of entire resolution necessary. Embassy
                    informed by Foreign Office that <persName corresp="#p_RYCKMANSP1"
                        >Ryckmans</persName>, with support <persName corresp="#p_LANGENHOVEF1">Van
                        Langenhove</persName> and other senior members Belgian delegation,
                    originally proposed that no Belgians should be present when Puerto Rican
                    resolution came to vote, but Foreign Office disapproved this proposal,
                    instructing delegation to attend but to abstain.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office said that it has been fully informed our views by <persName
                        corresp="#p_RYCKMANSP1">Ryckmans</persName>. Foreign Office emphasized that
                    Belgian position has been made clear repeatedly in <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> and that Belgium could not afford in this instance to deviate so
                    sharply as to permit it to vote with US.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Alger</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
